#: ../../../user/how-to-io.rst:272
msgid "Write or read large arrays"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-io.rst:274
msgid ""
"**Arrays too large to fit in memory** can be treated like ordinary in-memory "
"arrays using memory mapping."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-io.rst:277
msgid ""
"Raw array data written with :func:`numpy.ndarray.tofile` or :func:`numpy."
"ndarray.tobytes` can be read with :func:`numpy.memmap`::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-io.rst:280
msgid ""
"array = numpy.memmap(\"mydata/myarray.arr\", mode=\"r\", dtype=np.int16, "
"shape=(1024, 1024))"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-io.rst:282
msgid ""
"Files output by :func:`numpy.save` (that is, using the numpy format) can be "
"read using :func:`numpy.load` with the ``mmap_mode`` keyword argument::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-io.rst:285
msgid ""
"large_array[some_slice] = np.load(\"path/to/small_array\", mmap_mode=\"r\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-io.rst:287
msgid ""
"Memory mapping lacks features like data chunking and compression; more full-"
"featured formats and libraries usable with NumPy include:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-io.rst:290
msgid ""
"**HDF5**: `h5py <https://www.h5py.org/>`_ or `PyTables <https://www.pytables."
"org/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-io.rst:291
msgid ""
"**Zarr**: `here <https://zarr.readthedocs.io/en/stable/tutorial.html#reading-"
"and-writing-data>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-io.rst:292
msgid "**NetCDF**: :class:`scipy.io.netcdf_file`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-io.rst:294
msgid ""
"For tradeoffs among memmap, Zarr, and HDF5, see `pythonspeed.com <https://"
"pythonspeed.com/articles/mmap-vs-zarr-hdf5/>`_."
msgstr ""

